<subSubSection id="525FE83445D146BDA18B26AAEF22D69B" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="8B3AE22CC4DBE48F9F8F340700DCCDF6" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25B2E7C6B68FDE3E9C2AE8C5323C8959" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">
The suitable habitat for 
<taxonomicName id="B5779258D3D6415557432801A857CA35" authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Lorence (Syst. Bot. 30: 832" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="Lorence &amp; J. Florence" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Kadua" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Gentianales" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tahuatensis">
<emphasis id="814371D6C317B8D2363DCACEFAA1F374" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Kadua tahuatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on Tahuata (
<emphasis id="5EEA6DD40EC2DAB41A7DD5A5C784AB12" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">c.</emphasis>
61 km2) is indicated as an endangered environment, threatened by feral animals and invasive plants, reducing the extent of the forest. This species is extremely rare, with only five plants known from two localities. Following the criteria and categories of 
<bibRefCitation id="C5D1305B9BEB785AF0A94ACE5E7B3723" author="IUCN," journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" refId="B6" refString="IUCN, , 2001. IUCN Red List categories (version 3.1). IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland, Switzerland." title="IUCN Red List categories (version 3.1). IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland, Switzerland." year="2001">IUCN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
it is assigned a preliminary status of 
<emphasis id="33801D0CC9F934696971B4549EC016A8" bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Critically Endangered</emphasis>
(CR): B2a, B2b (i-iii); D: B2: total area of occupancy less than 10 km2 (ca. 5 km2). B2a, a single population known; b (
<normalizedToken id="59DDFC449D4FA5C0BCEECF9AD397C9F9" originalValue="i–iii">i-iii</normalizedToken>
), habitat continuing decline inferred; D, population estimated to number fewer than 250 individuals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C8945D2EFB598E97A25FA3D7B4262034" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" type="specimen examined">
<paragraph id="ED0B43E6E6283C3BED5B7CA0A0AE421B" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Specimens examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C3D67A331A3E77CABDC41952619CE52D" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis id="807256CCF74F308DD8EDD466791333B6" bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Marquesas Islands:</emphasis>
Tahuata: ridge between Amatea and Haaoiputeomo, southeast-facing slopes over Hanatetena village, 2740 ft. (835 m) elevation, 11 July 1997, Perlman 15954 (P, PAP, PTBG, US).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D4B8A05D7EF889E74B9A901FB8C0F52D" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B60334CD6F4E06CBCD5813E0EF0EEF3" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="20213DB2B90C1DDBCDF9FC721084C0E7" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">
Morphologically 
<taxonomicName id="619FD537058B221E061F212B9880FB4A" authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Lorence (Syst. Bot. 30: 832" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="Lorence &amp; J. Florence" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Kadua" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Gentianales" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tahuatensis">
<emphasis id="AC6EA5CB88787ABE08554EDF1B296AA8" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Kadua tahuatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="847190CE4C9509A33B6C463CFF78ED59" authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Lorence, Syst. Bot. 30: 832" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="Lorence &amp; J. Florence" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Kadua" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Gentianales" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nukuhivensis">
<emphasis id="D73BD74D475D560E3741B4D7F8F71AAF" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Kadua nukuhivensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and molecular evidence places these two as sister species in the same clade as 
<taxonomicName id="5DB46507DABE5FBF6D05B62123218C41" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Kadua" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Gentianales" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rapensis">
<emphasis id="FAA3466D5F1FB6E0610B911C442CA8E2" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Kadua rapensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
F. Br. and 
<taxonomicName id="AD97938C60D90175376F4CD9BB9940EA" authorityName="Cham &amp; Schltdl" authorityYear="1829" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Kadua" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Gentianales" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="romanzoffiensis">
<emphasis id="2202290A62D15C30B75B1F7D78F07A17" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="134">Kadua romanzoffiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cham. &amp; Schltdl. within the larger clade of Hawaiian and French Polynesian species (
<bibRefCitation id="5ED99A9D6BFB6D846868845CD365F98F" author="Motley, TJ" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="9" pageNumber="134" pagination="88 - 89" publicationUrl="http://www.2003.botanyconference.org/engine/search/detail.php?aid377" refId="B10" refString="Motley, TJ, 2003. Phylogeny of Hawaiian and Pacific Hedyotis (Rubiaceae): fruit evolution and the implications for conservation and genomics. In: Abstracts of Annual Meeting, Mobile, Alabama, Botany 2003.: 88 - 89, http://www.2003.botanyconference.org/engine/search/detail.php?aid377" title="Phylogeny of Hawaiian and Pacific Hedyotis (Rubiaceae): fruit evolution and the implications for conservation and genomics." url="http://www.2003.botanyconference.org/engine/search/detail.php?aid377" volumeTitle="Abstracts of Annual Meeting, Mobile, Alabama, Botany 2003." year="2003">Motley 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
